01:18:06.728 --> 01:18:09.188
Do you ever cut your hands
when you're wringing?

01:18:09.231 --> 01:18:11.691
Joanne, that is so funny
that you said that.

01:18:11.733 --> 01:18:16.243
That is actually exactly how
I was inspired to invent this mop.

01:18:16.280 --> 01:18:21.490
There was glass shattered everywhere.
I was with my two kids, with my father, and I...

01:18:21.535 --> 01:18:24.795
Every time I would wring the mop,
I would get glass shards in my hands.

01:18:25.247 --> 01:18:28.417
And the old mop
just wasn't very absorbent.

01:18:28.458 --> 01:18:33.668
So I went to my daughter's room,
and I borrowed her crayons...

01:18:33.714 --> 01:18:36.304
and I designed this mop.

01:18:36.925 --> 01:18:38.085
Make sure you get down there.
Yeah, that's it.

01:18:38.468 --> 01:18:40.828
It's made of plastic, so it's lightweight,
but very durable.

01:18:41.096 --> 01:18:42.506
Go in. Go in to the hands.

01:18:42.556 --> 01:18:43.516
It's extremely absorbent...

01:18:43.557 --> 01:18:46.097
with 300 continuous cotton loops...

01:18:46.143 --> 01:18:48.483
that I looped myself
when I designed it.

01:18:48.770 --> 01:18:51.770
- How much is it?
- It is $19.95.

01:18:52.316 --> 01:18:54.316
I like that price.
I want a whole bunch of them.

01:18:55.068 --> 01:18:56.318
Thank you.

01:18:56.570 --> 01:18:58.530
H375. That's the order number.

01:18:58.572 --> 01:19:00.782
Household item 375.

01:19:00.824 --> 01:19:01.954
I guarantee you...

01:19:01.992 --> 01:19:03.282
That's it. Stay right there.

01:19:03.327 --> 01:19:05.537
...you are not going to find
another mop like this that exists.

01:19:05.579 --> 01:19:08.919
If there was, I would have bought it
and I wouldn't have cut my hands up.

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:13.920
You can get across the whole kitchen
with one wring. Just imagine that.

01:19:13.962 --> 01:19:15.302
Watch this.

01:19:16.465 --> 01:19:17.925
Chocolate syrup.

01:19:20.093 --> 01:19:21.393
Go the syrup. Go the syrup.

01:19:21.428 --> 01:19:24.138
Baby food.
A very big spill at my house.

01:19:24.181 --> 01:19:25.561
Very common spill for me.

01:19:25.599 --> 01:19:27.179
No. Hands, hands.

01:19:27.809 --> 01:19:31.729
Now, the biggest difference,
I don't have to touch this disgusting mop head.

01:19:31.772 --> 01:19:33.772
There's not another mop on the market...

01:19:33.815 --> 01:19:38.485
that has as much absorbent cotton
as this mop right here.

01:19:38.529 --> 01:19:42.449
And I guarantee you,
there will be no regrets, no returns.

01:19:42.491 --> 01:19:45.661
I have been mopping for most of my life,
every single day.

01:19:45.702 --> 01:19:46.832
Phones are ringing!

01:19:46.870 --> 01:19:49.120
I cannot tell you how much
this mop has changed my life.

01:19:49.164 --> 01:19:51.124
- Phones are ringing! Phones are ringing!
- The phones are ringing. The phones are ringing.

01:19:51.375 --> 01:19:52.045
Go.

01:19:52.292 --> 01:19:55.422
This is gonna be the greatest mop
to have around Christmas time...

01:19:55.462 --> 01:19:57.462
when you have family over...

01:19:57.506 --> 01:20:01.586
I am a mother of two.
There is just spill after spill.

01:20:01.635 --> 01:20:03.435
Family comes to town.

01:20:03.470 --> 01:20:05.890
You can mop your entire kitchen
with one wring!

01:20:06.139 --> 01:20:08.889
Oh, my God! 29,000!

01:20:09.142 --> 01:20:10.772
This is very special!

01:20:10.811 --> 01:20:13.521
I haven't even told you about
my personal favorite feature...

01:20:13.564 --> 01:20:15.694
which is the removable mop head...

01:20:15.732 --> 01:20:20.702
that I can put into the washing machine
and it will come out clean as new.

01:20:20.737 --> 01:20:22.237
Yes! Yes!

01:20:22.281 --> 01:20:24.621
Oh, my God, these numbers keep climbing!

01:20:25.576 --> 01:20:26.866
Thank you. I...

01:20:26.910 --> 01:20:28.240
Yes, that's right. Keep it going.

01:20:28.287 --> 01:20:29.287
Thank you.

01:20:30.622 --> 01:20:33.582
This is the most absorbent
mop on the market. It's lightweight.

01:20:33.625 --> 01:20:37.045
It's the only mop that you're ever gonna buy,
the best mop you're ever gonna use.

01:20:37.087 --> 01:20:41.507
It is lightweight and durable, and that is
just me speaking from my experience.

01:20:41.550 --> 01:20:45.600
As someone who mops their house
every single day, from my heart.

01:20:46.930 --> 01:20:50.100
This woman's gonna be
a whole new business.

01:20:51.977 --> 01:20:52.977
No way.

01:20:58.400 --> 01:20:59.730
Oh, my God.

01:21:19.922 --> 01:21:23.432
Can you believe it?
Can you believe it?

01:21:23.467 --> 01:21:26.967
I thought for sure you were gonna tell me
that your counting machine was broken.

01:21:27.012 --> 01:21:28.812
I listened to you. You were right.

01:21:28.847 --> 01:21:31.467
I just can't believe
that actually happened.

01:21:31.517 --> 01:21:32.637
I know.

01:21:32.684 --> 01:21:35.234
I guess you could say
we're friends in commerce.

01:21:35.270 --> 01:21:36.440
Friends in commerce.

01:21:36.480 --> 01:21:37.440
Yeah.

01:21:37.481 --> 01:21:41.111
Let's promise each other that if, one day,
and that day may come...

01:21:41.151 --> 01:21:44.611
that we become adversaries in commerce,
that we remain friends.

01:21:44.655 --> 01:21:46.415
Because that's a true friendship indeed.

01:21:46.448 --> 01:21:47.698
Friends in commerce.

01:21:48.325 --> 01:21:50.335
I agree. Let's shake on it.

01:22:31.076 --> 01:22:33.036
We've got 10 looms...

01:22:33.078 --> 01:22:36.618
and then when they're completed,
this is where the mop heads are sewn.

01:22:38.834 --> 01:22:40.174
Who makes your parts?

01:22:40.669 --> 01:22:42.499
A factory out in California.

01:22:42.546 --> 01:22:45.336
It was cheaper and faster
than any place around here.

01:22:45.382 --> 01:22:47.722
Smart. Are they gonna be able
to stay on schedule?

01:22:49.178 --> 01:22:50.178
Yeah.

01:22:57.227 --> 01:22:58.437
One time.

01:23:18.123 --> 01:23:19.253
- Right there.
- Thank you.

01:23:19.291 --> 01:23:20.491
- You're welcome.
- Right here?

01:23:22.252 --> 01:23:23.252
Hello?

01:24:24.314 --> 01:24:25.444
Mimi.

01:24:28.277 --> 01:24:29.357
Mimi.

01:24:44.626 --> 01:24:46.996
I so hated to leave her that day.

01:24:48.172 --> 01:24:50.762
I had so much I wanted to say to her.

01:24:51.675 --> 01:24:53.715
And to my great granddaughter.

01:24:56.471 --> 01:25:01.561
I felt I wanted to stay near her
and watch over her.

01:26:07.668 --> 01:26:09.288
Cristy.

01:26:15.384 --> 01:26:17.344
There's a problem in California.

01:26:17.386 --> 01:26:21.636
There can't be a problem in California.
I told Neil that everything was fine.

01:26:21.682 --> 01:26:24.812
Gerhardt keeps raising his price.
He just did it again.

01:26:24.852 --> 01:26:25.852
More money per unit.

01:26:27.229 --> 01:26:29.309
He can't do that.
We're gonna lose money.

01:26:29.356 --> 01:26:31.476
I sent a representative to handle him.

01:26:32.693 --> 01:26:34.653
Representative?
We don't have a representative.

01:26:34.695 --> 01:26:36.245
What representative?

01:26:36.780 --> 01:26:37.990
Peggy went.

01:26:38.282 --> 01:26:39.412
Peggy?

01:26:43.871 --> 01:26:45.831
I don't want to talk about this
right now.

01:26:54.798 --> 01:26:56.168
She wanted to be part of it.

01:26:56.216 --> 01:26:58.216
How could you send Peggy?

01:27:02.931 --> 01:27:04.891
She wanted to be part of it.

01:27:05.726 --> 01:27:09.936
You both are blood relatives.
You're half-sisters.

01:27:09.980 --> 01:27:13.730
It's very, very important
that you love and respect each other.

01:27:16.236 --> 01:27:20.526
I paid them the 20
that you owed them. I had to.

01:27:22.284 --> 01:27:25.914
I got them to fill the order
of the 100,000...

01:27:25.954 --> 01:27:28.584
with a price increase
of only two dollars per unit.

01:27:28.624 --> 01:27:33.214
We can't increase at all, Peggy.
Don't you understand?

01:27:35.464 --> 01:27:38.174
We sold at a certain price.

01:27:39.009 --> 01:27:42.759
Any hikes,
especially the ones he's asking for...

01:27:42.804 --> 01:27:44.814
mean that I will lose so much money...

01:27:44.848 --> 01:27:49.098
that I'll be in even more debt
than I was before.

01:27:51.146 --> 01:27:52.766
You're gonna make it back.

01:27:53.607 --> 01:27:55.727
I'm gonna make it back?

01:27:56.568 --> 01:27:57.568
How?

01:28:02.741 --> 01:28:04.831
I've got ideas, you know.

01:28:06.828 --> 01:28:09.248
There are things that I'd like to do.

01:28:09.289 --> 01:28:13.079
I spoke to him about a project
that Dad and I have been designing.

01:28:13.126 --> 01:28:14.416
Right, Dad?

01:28:14.461 --> 01:28:15.921
Yes, we did.

01:28:18.048 --> 01:28:22.838
Do you have any idea
how much your idea will cost?

01:28:22.886 --> 01:28:24.966
How or where you'll sell it?

01:28:25.639 --> 01:28:28.929
If you can even manufacture it
after it's taken everything we've got...

01:28:28.976 --> 01:28:32.596
to sell this one product that now,
thanks to you...

01:28:32.646 --> 01:28:34.646
is going to cost more money?

01:28:35.274 --> 01:28:38.114
Maybe my product
is better than your product.

01:28:38.151 --> 01:28:40.701
I can do what you did on TV.
It's not that hard.

01:28:40.737 --> 01:28:44.317
Isn't that the whole purpose of that channel?
It's that everybody could do it?

01:28:45.534 --> 01:28:50.504
What your sister does is not easy...

01:28:50.539 --> 01:28:54.499
but what we were planning to do...

01:28:54.543 --> 01:28:58.213
is not that difficult.

01:28:59.214 --> 01:29:00.974
Listen to me.

01:29:01.925 --> 01:29:07.385
Never speak on my behalf...

01:29:10.100 --> 01:29:13.480
about my business again.

01:29:15.439 --> 01:29:18.109
Now I have to go to California.

01:30:19.253 --> 01:30:20.553
Can I help you?

01:30:20.587 --> 01:30:22.587
I'm Joy. I'm here to see Gerhardt.

01:30:23.298 --> 01:30:24.758
He's not available.

01:30:25.968 --> 01:30:27.138
I'll wait.

01:30:30.597 --> 01:30:32.887
She says she's here to see Gerhardt.

01:30:33.851 --> 01:30:34.851
Gerhardt!

01:30:42.693 --> 01:30:44.783
Hey. I'm Gerhardt.

01:30:44.820 --> 01:30:46.320
I'm Joy.

01:30:46.363 --> 01:30:47.743
Come on in.

01:30:47.781 --> 01:30:49.201
Derek Markham is my boss.

01:30:49.241 --> 01:30:50.491
He lives in Texas.

01:30:50.534 --> 01:30:54.914
Fabri-Pac is one of several companies
he owns or collects royalties for.

01:30:54.955 --> 01:30:58.465
I report to him.
He makes pricing decisions.

01:30:58.500 --> 01:31:01.590
Well, I've never met or talked
to this Derek Markham...

01:31:01.628 --> 01:31:03.418
but I've talked to you many times
on the phone.

01:31:03.463 --> 01:31:05.013
And I do find it very curious...

01:31:05.048 --> 01:31:08.128
that the second I'm on television,
with a lot of success...

01:31:08.177 --> 01:31:10.597
the price for our products goes up.

01:31:10.637 --> 01:31:13.307
Seems very unfair to me,
to say the least.

01:31:14.016 --> 01:31:16.386
Seems like you're shaking us down.

01:31:16.435 --> 01:31:18.855
You met Gregory, our plant foreman.

01:31:18.896 --> 01:31:21.186
It's very hard for us to lower the cost
at this point.

01:31:21.690 --> 01:31:23.980
We're already losing a lot of money.

01:31:24.026 --> 01:31:27.196
How could that possibly be,
with the $500,000 that we've given you...

01:31:27.237 --> 01:31:29.527
on top of the
$50,000 of advance royalties...

01:31:29.573 --> 01:31:32.833
that have gone to a Derek Markham
in Dallas.

01:31:32.868 --> 01:31:35.118
And that's not even counting
what my sister paid you...

01:31:35.162 --> 01:31:36.832
without my authority, by the way...

01:31:36.872 --> 01:31:39.582
for your overcharges and your mistakes.

01:31:40.334 --> 01:31:43.924
Your sister paid the increase
that you refused to pay.

01:31:44.254 --> 01:31:48.094
Well, she had no authority to do that.
She's not an officer of my corporation.

01:31:49.092 --> 01:31:53.602
You and I could both spend a lot of time
and money in court to prove that I'm right...

01:31:54.765 --> 01:31:56.525
but that would just make
our lawyers wealthy...

01:31:56.558 --> 01:31:59.098
while my product dies
instead of being on television...

01:31:59.144 --> 01:32:00.944
like it could be right now.

01:32:02.022 --> 01:32:03.652
You can pay more.

01:32:04.149 --> 01:32:06.899
I can't pay more. I won't.

01:32:06.944 --> 01:32:09.864
Costs are higher.
Wear and tear on the molds.

01:32:09.905 --> 01:32:11.995
We have to remake them every other week.

01:32:12.032 --> 01:32:14.992
Is that so? Can I see the molds?

01:32:15.035 --> 01:32:16.575
They're in the machines.

01:32:16.620 --> 01:32:19.460
It'll take some time
to prepare them for you.

01:32:24.378 --> 01:32:26.378
Is there a bathroom I could use?

01:32:29.591 --> 01:32:31.891
Yeah, it's down the hall.
Gregory will show you.

01:32:40.102 --> 01:32:41.192
Thanks.

01:34:02.184 --> 01:34:03.314
What?

01:34:07.147 --> 01:34:08.687
What are you doing in here?

01:34:09.316 --> 01:34:10.726
What is this?

01:34:10.776 --> 01:34:13.776
These are my designs,
these are my molds!

01:34:13.820 --> 01:34:14.950
Those are ours!

01:34:14.988 --> 01:34:17.068
And we knew you'd be trouble.
The cops are on their way.

01:34:17.115 --> 01:34:19.365
- We called 'em as soon as you showed up!
- These are my molds!

01:34:19.409 --> 01:34:20.619
Those are ours!

01:34:20.661 --> 01:34:22.541
I'm taking these with me.

01:34:22.788 --> 01:34:24.118
I'm taking all of these with me.

01:34:24.164 --> 01:34:26.584
I want all of these boxed up,
and I'm taking them.

01:34:26.625 --> 01:34:27.885
You're trespassing!

01:34:27.918 --> 01:34:29.168
It's not your patent!

01:34:29.586 --> 01:34:31.496
These are my designs!

01:34:32.840 --> 01:34:35.180
I'm not going anywhere without my molds.

01:34:36.093 --> 01:34:37.803
What? No. No.

01:34:37.845 --> 01:34:40.265
This is not stealing,
this is my property!

01:34:40.305 --> 01:34:41.555
This is my property.

01:34:41.598 --> 01:34:45.058
I have all of these designs.
These are all mine. They belong to me!

01:34:45.102 --> 01:34:48.862
She's from out of state, John!
You've known me 15 years!

01:34:48.897 --> 01:34:50.647
All right, come on, ma'am.
You're trespassing.

01:34:50.691 --> 01:34:52.401
- What?
- Yeah. Come on.

01:34:52.442 --> 01:34:53.942
- I'm not trespassing.
- Yeah, you're trespassing.

01:34:53.986 --> 01:34:55.106
I was in his office.

01:34:55.153 --> 01:34:56.653
- You don't know. Come on.
- He let me into his...

01:34:56.697 --> 01:34:58.197
Gerhardt, you're not gonna
get away with this.

01:34:58.240 --> 01:34:59.780
- You're not gonna get away with this!
- Be careful what you're saying.

01:34:59.825 --> 01:35:01.875
- You're a thief! You're a thief, Gerhardt!
- Be careful, come on, come on.

01:35:01.910 --> 01:35:03.240
Be careful. Come on, stop it.

01:35:03.287 --> 01:35:05.497
- This is stealing!
- Hey, hey, stop it. Come on.

01:35:05.539 --> 01:35:06.539
All right.

01:35:09.626 --> 01:35:11.586
Watch your step. All right.

01:35:19.636 --> 01:35:21.006
What about Trudy's money, Joy?

01:35:21.054 --> 01:35:23.184
You have to pay back Trudy's money.

01:35:23.223 --> 01:35:24.893
This is only getting worse.

01:35:24.933 --> 01:35:26.813
I predicted tragedy, Joy.

01:35:27.269 --> 01:35:29.309
You're racking up quite a steep bill.

01:35:29.354 --> 01:35:32.614
We had to fly out here, bail you out.

01:35:32.649 --> 01:35:35.779
Plus it cost us an extra $10,000
for Ray Cagney...

01:35:35.819 --> 01:35:38.319
this California patent attorney,
to get us to this point.

01:35:38.363 --> 01:35:40.993
We got the state to decline prosecution.

01:35:41.033 --> 01:35:43.243
They see it's a contract dispute.

01:35:43.285 --> 01:35:46.915
When you paid royalties
to Derek Markham in Texas...

01:35:46.955 --> 01:35:50.995
it put all your parts and molds
under the umbrella of their patent.

01:35:51.919 --> 01:35:55.169
I see you brought your drawings
and hung them to prove your design.

01:35:55.214 --> 01:35:57.844
But it's impossible to fight it now.

01:35:57.883 --> 01:36:00.343
You were not properly advised.

01:36:01.678 --> 01:36:03.178
Cristy, please!

01:36:03.222 --> 01:36:04.352
Tony, take her to bed.

01:36:04.389 --> 01:36:06.639
I don't wanna go to bed.
I wanna stay here.

01:36:06.683 --> 01:36:08.183
I paid those royalties...

01:36:08.227 --> 01:36:09.347
because you told me to.

01:36:09.394 --> 01:36:12.234
Because your lawyer told me to.

01:36:12.272 --> 01:36:16.152
Our lawyer was mistaken.
This happens sometimes in business.

01:36:16.193 --> 01:36:17.533
It didn't work out for you.

01:36:17.569 --> 01:36:18.739
It happens sometimes.

01:36:18.779 --> 01:36:20.239
Trudy's lawyer is not a patent attorney.

01:36:20.280 --> 01:36:21.740
Which I said!

01:36:21.782 --> 01:36:25.872
And you said I had no business
being Joy's advisor.

01:36:25.911 --> 01:36:27.791
- And now it turns out that I was right!
- This is not helpful, Tony!

01:36:27.829 --> 01:36:29.869
- That's enough, Tony. Please.
- It's enough, now?

01:36:29.915 --> 01:36:32.675
I'm very sorry.
I wish there was more I could do.

01:36:32.709 --> 01:36:35.919
But when your sister Peggy paid
the unjustified bills...

01:36:35.963 --> 01:36:37.803
that you refused to pay...

01:36:37.840 --> 01:36:39.420
it closed the door on that.

01:36:39.466 --> 01:36:41.296
What about Neil Walker and QVC?

01:36:41.343 --> 01:36:43.853
Wouldn't they pay the expenses
on defending the patent?

01:36:44.596 --> 01:36:45.716
Be careful, Joy.

01:36:45.764 --> 01:36:49.524
You could be sued for misrepresentation
and failure to deliver your product.

01:36:49.560 --> 01:36:50.560
That's breach.

01:36:51.520 --> 01:36:54.900
QVC requires that you deliver
a fully patented product.

01:36:54.940 --> 01:36:57.440
I've been doing this for a long time.

01:36:57.484 --> 01:37:01.574
You're in for a long court process
that will stall your product.

01:37:01.613 --> 01:37:03.203
And you will probably lose.

01:37:03.240 --> 01:37:04.660
I wish I could do more.

01:37:06.285 --> 01:37:07.835
Take care, now.

01:37:07.870 --> 01:37:10.210
You're gonna have to accept
the facts, Joy.

01:37:10.247 --> 01:37:11.707
I mean, that's...

01:37:12.332 --> 01:37:14.422
You're most of half a million dollars
in debt.

01:37:14.459 --> 01:37:16.289
I don't know how you're gonna pay it.

01:37:16.628 --> 01:37:18.418
We have to declare bankruptcy.

01:37:18.463 --> 01:37:20.883
You're gonna have to declare bankruptcy.

01:37:21.258 --> 01:37:22.548
I have to declare bankruptcy.

01:37:22.593 --> 01:37:23.723
She has to.

01:37:23.760 --> 01:37:25.300
- To try to contain my losses.
- Yeah.

01:37:25.345 --> 01:37:26.635
I have to write it off.

01:37:26.680 --> 01:37:28.720
It just seems so wrong.

01:37:28.765 --> 01:37:30.425
We've worked so hard.

01:37:30.475 --> 01:37:32.685
We've come so far
for us to just give up now.

01:37:32.728 --> 01:37:34.308
It just seems so unfair!

01:37:34.354 --> 01:37:36.984
Business is unfair. That's it.

01:37:37.024 --> 01:37:39.154
It's not working out.
Well, that's what happens.

01:37:39.193 --> 01:37:43.033
That's why people don't go around
making invention every other day.

01:37:43.071 --> 01:37:44.161
Wake up!

01:37:44.198 --> 01:37:45.318
It's my fault.

01:37:45.365 --> 01:37:48.275
I gave her the confidence to think she was
more than just an unemployed housewife...

01:37:48.327 --> 01:37:51.157
selling plastic kitchen stuff
to other unemployed housewives...

01:37:51.205 --> 01:37:52.415
on a junk cable channel.

01:37:52.456 --> 01:37:55.286
It's my fault.
It's not your fault, honey.

01:37:55.334 --> 01:37:57.974
It was my mistake to make her think
that she was more than she was.

01:37:58.378 --> 01:38:00.958
She pressured herself into doing
something she shouldn't have done.

01:38:01.006 --> 01:38:03.166
It was wrong of you
to put that pressure on yourself.

01:38:03.217 --> 01:38:05.547
It was wrong of us
to put that pressure on you.

01:38:05.594 --> 01:38:07.184
I need more vodka.

01:38:07.221 --> 01:38:12.981
It was wrong of us to think that you'd be
an instant business person overnight.

01:38:13.018 --> 01:38:15.558
Of course, this is not who you are.

01:38:16.522 --> 01:38:21.612
It takes a kind of toughness,
a certain acumen...

01:38:21.652 --> 01:38:24.452
that you simply don't have.

01:38:25.113 --> 01:38:26.453
Sign the paper.

01:38:30.994 --> 01:38:33.584
You have to sign
these bankruptcy papers, honey.

01:38:33.622 --> 01:38:36.172
The notary's right outside.
Let me get her.

01:38:40.170 --> 01:38:42.370
You're gonna have to move
out of your house immediately.

01:38:43.173 --> 01:38:44.893
You're gonna have to move
into an apartment.

01:38:45.342 --> 01:38:47.552
Maybe you can move into a room
in Trudy's house.

01:38:47.594 --> 01:38:48.854
With the children?

01:38:48.887 --> 01:38:50.257
Yeah. You have room.

01:38:51.181 --> 01:38:52.601
She's my daughter. Why not?

01:38:53.934 --> 01:38:55.524
Let's talk about it.

01:38:56.019 --> 01:38:57.649
Trudy, we have to offer her something.

01:38:57.688 --> 01:38:58.808
Again?

01:38:58.856 --> 01:39:00.066
Why me?

01:39:07.865 --> 01:39:09.455
Please sign, honey.

01:39:35.767 --> 01:39:36.887
Thank you.

01:39:40.647 --> 01:39:45.067
Mimi said you were the one born
to help carry the family to success.

01:39:48.572 --> 01:39:51.412
No, Cristy. Mimi was wrong.

01:39:52.826 --> 01:39:55.196
The world does not give you opportunities.

01:39:55.245 --> 01:39:59.995
The world destroys your opportunity
and it breaks your heart.

01:40:00.626 --> 01:40:04.376
I should have listened to my mother
when I was 10 years old.

01:40:04.421 --> 01:40:06.101
I should have spent the rest of my life...

01:40:06.131 --> 01:40:09.181
watching TV and hiding from the world
like my mother.

01:40:10.093 --> 01:40:12.683
So I don't wanna hear
any more about Mimi.

01:40:13.263 --> 01:40:14.433
She was wrong.

01:40:14.473 --> 01:40:18.063
She had her head in the clouds
and it was full of stupid ideas.

01:40:18.101 --> 01:40:20.271
And it gave me stupid ideas.

01:40:22.814 --> 01:40:23.824
Like this.

01:40:26.652 --> 01:40:28.822
This stupid, stupid idea!

01:40:31.782 --> 01:40:34.332
Mommy, don't tear them! No!

01:40:56.056 --> 01:40:58.346
Cristy, I'm so sorry.

01:40:58.392 --> 01:41:00.602
I'm sorry, Cristy.

01:41:00.644 --> 01:41:02.314
I'm so sorry.

01:41:02.354 --> 01:41:04.814
Please go to bed.
Everybody just go to bed.

01:41:06.191 --> 01:41:07.941
Good night, Mommy.

01:41:07.985 --> 01:41:10.155
Good night, sweetheart. Just go to bed.

01:41:12.739 --> 01:41:15.239
I'm so sorry I failed you, Joy.
I'm so sorry.

01:41:15.492 --> 01:41:17.082
Just, just don't.

01:42:48.752 --> 01:42:50.962
Joy? Joy?

01:42:51.630 --> 01:42:53.050
Joy, where are you?

01:42:55.050 --> 01:42:56.800
Joy, where are you?

01:44:10.501 --> 01:44:11.791
It's open.

01:44:19.551 --> 01:44:20.891
You can leave the door open.

01:44:46.870 --> 01:44:48.870
No one knows I'm here.

01:44:49.873 --> 01:44:52.003
You don't even know who I am.

01:44:52.042 --> 01:44:57.552
I could be Derek Markham or I might be
someone Derek Markham sent to handle you.

01:44:58.048 --> 01:45:00.048
You have no case.

01:45:00.551 --> 01:45:04.551
Maybe people think you came to Dallas
in despair to take your own life...

01:45:04.596 --> 01:45:09.556
because you were in such deep financial
trouble suddenly from your little venture.

01:45:16.233 --> 01:45:19.533
I made a phone call this morning
to Hong Kong.

01:45:20.195 --> 01:45:25.365
It was 1:00 a.m. in California but it was 5:00 p.m.
the following afternoon in Hong Kong.

01:45:25.409 --> 01:45:29.749
I always think it's amazing
how time works like that.

01:45:31.456 --> 01:45:34.706
And I was fortunate enough to get
on the phone with Mr. Christopher...

01:45:34.751 --> 01:45:37.921
who I found to be very friendly,
which was surprising...

01:45:37.963 --> 01:45:41.223
because I really haven't found the
gentlemen in California to be very nice...

01:45:41.258 --> 01:45:43.758
considering we're all
in business together.

01:45:43.802 --> 01:45:47.602
Welcome to the world of business,
I guess.

01:45:48.640 --> 01:45:51.060
I told Mr. Christopher
that the reason that I was calling...

01:45:51.101 --> 01:45:55.111
was to discuss the differences
in the designs of our products.

01:45:55.772 --> 01:46:00.242
But I quickly learned
that Mr. Christopher has no idea...

01:46:00.277 --> 01:46:06.447
if his Hong Kong patent for a self-wringing
mop is worth anything or if it even works.

01:46:07.075 --> 01:46:12.115
Because they have not made
or sold a single mop.

01:46:12.414 --> 01:46:16.134
Unlike us, who have sold over 200,000.

01:46:17.252 --> 01:46:22.132
And I've paid you over $50,000
in advanced royalties...

01:46:22.174 --> 01:46:24.134
on behalf of Mr. Christopher.

01:46:24.676 --> 01:46:29.596
Blood money from my family
and my second mortgage.

01:46:30.849 --> 01:46:35.309
Turns out Mr. Christopher doesn't know
anything about those royalties.

01:46:35.354 --> 01:46:36.814
So it seems...

01:46:37.981 --> 01:46:41.611
we have a case of fraud and embezzlement.

01:46:44.655 --> 01:46:47.825
And, as if that weren't bad enough...

01:46:48.700 --> 01:46:54.330
I also discovered in the paperwork that
our mops actually don't bear any similarities.

01:46:54.373 --> 01:46:57.503
So I never did owe you
any royalties for your patent.

01:46:58.544 --> 01:47:00.504
That's another case of fraud.

01:47:01.171 --> 01:47:07.181
My lawyers really could go after you,
but I told them, "Give me a day."

01:47:07.219 --> 01:47:13.179
To see if maybe
you might've made a mistake...

01:47:15.018 --> 01:47:17.978
that you would correct,
given the chance.

01:47:33.370 --> 01:47:36.370
We'll pay you back all the royalties
you paid us.

01:47:41.420 --> 01:47:46.050
I'll give you $20,000
on top of paying you back the 50.

01:47:58.020 --> 01:47:59.230
Okay.

01:48:00.939 --> 01:48:04.689
I'll give you $50,000
on top of paying you back the 50.

01:48:16.747 --> 01:48:18.367
Plus interest.

01:48:23.795 --> 01:48:25.795
I want all of my molds back.

01:48:26.465 --> 01:48:28.765
I want you to sign
this piece of paper...

01:48:29.801 --> 01:48:33.101
saying that you have
no rights, financially.

01:48:34.097 --> 01:48:37.597
I'm just gonna add...
I said the 50...

01:48:39.728 --> 01:48:41.648
plus the 50...

01:48:43.440 --> 01:48:46.230
plus the interest.

01:48:46.276 --> 01:48:50.406
So I just want you to initial
next to those two numbers as well.

01:48:56.453 --> 01:48:57.953
So just sign there.

01:49:05.963 --> 01:49:08.473
She put up with just about anything.

01:49:09.466 --> 01:49:11.926
Until when she had to
bring the hammer down...

01:49:13.470 --> 01:49:15.140
she brought the hammer down.

01:49:17.474 --> 01:49:20.144
She couldn't know what was to come.

01:49:21.019 --> 01:49:25.109
That she'd go on to make
another 100 record-setting patents.

01:49:26.024 --> 01:49:29.744
Skinny velvet hangers
make neater closets.

01:49:29.778 --> 01:49:32.108
That's a big deal to a lot of people.

01:49:33.282 --> 01:49:35.702
I mean, who thinks of things like that?

01:49:36.869 --> 01:49:38.159
Joy did.

01:49:42.457 --> 01:49:47.667
She didn't know any of this would happen
as she walked down the street that day.

01:49:48.338 --> 01:49:52.468
Yes, sir, tonight's the night for
Ol' Saint Nick to make his yearly visit...

01:49:52.509 --> 01:49:54.639
to all the folks all over the world.

01:49:54.678 --> 01:49:58.308
There's fun and expectation
in every house across the land.

01:49:58.348 --> 01:50:02.438
And speaking of houses, what do you say
we take a little look-in on a typical one?

01:50:05.439 --> 01:50:10.989
Now I'll admit that what you see right now
is just a small piece of the front of the house...

01:50:11.028 --> 01:50:14.908
but all you grownups and kids alike,
this is the time for Santa's magic...

01:50:14.948 --> 01:50:18.158
so I think we can make it
become a real house.

01:50:19.036 --> 01:50:20.616
Even a house with love in it.

01:50:20.662 --> 01:50:23.712
Mr. Santa Claus, can we have
a little snow, please?

01:50:25.792 --> 01:50:27.712
Thank you. That's fine.

01:50:28.003 --> 01:50:32.053
Now, Santa, let me see what it
really looks like inside this house.

01:51:01.411 --> 01:51:05.921
She couldn't know that one day
she would move into a big beautiful home.

01:51:08.502 --> 01:51:10.752
Her mother was happy.

01:51:11.547 --> 01:51:15.877
She remained close to her,
and with the rest of her family...

01:51:15.926 --> 01:51:18.676
which was, as always, complicated.

01:51:20.848 --> 01:51:26.188
She would pay for products made by
Rudy, Trudy, and Peggy.

01:51:26.228 --> 01:51:28.268
Even when they failed.

01:51:28.939 --> 01:51:33.689
Even when they wrongly sued
for ownership of her company.

01:51:34.570 --> 01:51:39.280
As Rudy got older,
Joy continued to take care of him and love him.

01:51:45.122 --> 01:51:50.792
As Neil Walker predicted,
Joy did become a whole new business.

01:51:51.253 --> 01:51:53.343
And even outgrew QVC.

01:51:53.380 --> 01:51:55.340
- She's talking to her children.
- Is Tony in there?

01:51:55.424 --> 01:51:56.724
Yes, Tony's in there.
The family's in there.

01:51:56.967 --> 01:52:03.177
Her ex-husband and her best friend
would remain her steadfast advisers.

01:52:03.223 --> 01:52:04.563
Please be patient.

01:52:10.314 --> 01:52:12.614
I love you.
You guys go and pack your rooms.

01:52:12.649 --> 01:52:14.439
- Good night, Mom.
- I love you.

01:52:23.452 --> 01:52:24.702
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:52:24.745 --> 01:52:26.415
- Welcome.
- Thank you.

01:52:29.082 --> 01:52:30.292
What do you have?

01:52:30.334 --> 01:52:32.134
A traveling clothes cleaner.

01:52:32.169 --> 01:52:33.169
Let's see it.

01:52:34.129 --> 01:52:35.419
So you're from Memphis?

01:52:35.464 --> 01:52:36.804
Yes, I am.

01:52:36.840 --> 01:52:38.130
You work as a waitress?

01:52:38.175 --> 01:52:39.475
Yes, ma'am.

01:52:39.510 --> 01:52:42.010
All right. Let's see it.

01:52:43.514 --> 01:52:44.814
You made this yourself?

01:52:44.848 --> 01:52:45.848
Yes, I did, ma'am.

01:52:46.850 --> 01:52:49.100
I made my first invention myself, too.

01:52:50.521 --> 01:52:52.521
I like this, it's a very good design.

01:52:52.773 --> 01:52:53.773
Thank you.

01:52:53.815 --> 01:52:56.315
Can you stay an extra day,
meet with our designers?

01:52:57.152 --> 01:52:58.362
No, because of your boss?

01:52:59.988 --> 01:53:01.908
What hotel are you staying in right now?

01:53:01.949 --> 01:53:03.659
- The Holiday Inn, ma'am.
- Holiday Inn.

01:53:03.700 --> 01:53:05.790
Let's move them over to the Radisson,
get them a suite.

01:53:05.827 --> 01:53:07.497
You'll be more comfortable
with your baby.

01:53:07.538 --> 01:53:10.458
I'll call your boss and get it taken care of,
give you an extra day...

01:53:10.499 --> 01:53:12.780
so that tomorrow you can come in,
meet with the designers.

01:53:12.960 --> 01:53:14.710
- We can take it step by step, all right?
- Thank you.

01:53:14.962 --> 01:53:16.762
We'll work on your idea,
see if we can do something.

01:53:16.797 --> 01:53:18.627
This means so much to me.

01:53:18.882 --> 01:53:20.382
I know what it feels like.

01:53:20.843 --> 01:53:22.893
I know what it feels like
to be in that chair.

01:53:23.554 --> 01:53:25.604
- We'll see you tomorrow, okay?
- Thank you, ma'am.

01:53:25.639 --> 01:53:26.889
And good luck.

01:53:27.182 --> 01:53:28.642
- Thank you for coming.
- Thank you.

01:53:28.684 --> 01:53:31.394
- Go get the next person, Tony.
- Okay.

01:53:31.895 --> 01:53:32.895
Neil.

01:53:35.023 --> 01:53:37.153
Sorry, we have legal stuff
with Barry, now.

01:53:40.487 --> 01:53:41.907
Yes, we do.

01:53:43.323 --> 01:53:44.873
Here we are.

01:53:44.908 --> 01:53:46.078
Here we are.

01:53:47.703 --> 01:53:49.753
Adversaries in commerce.

01:53:50.581 --> 01:53:52.751
Adversaries in commerce.

01:53:53.917 --> 01:53:55.707
- And friends.
- Yes.

01:53:56.170 --> 01:53:57.380
And friends.

01:53:58.589 --> 01:54:01.259
I'm gonna tell you something
but you didn't hear it from me.

01:54:01.592 --> 01:54:03.842
I don't know who you are
or what you're talking about.

01:54:03.886 --> 01:54:05.506
That's what I wanted to hear.

01:54:07.264 --> 01:54:09.354
Barry's gonna come after you, hard.

01:54:09.391 --> 01:54:12.891
But that's just business.
That's the way Barry is. He's a negotiator.

01:54:12.936 --> 01:54:15.226
Ultimately, he needs you.

01:54:15.272 --> 01:54:18.572
He's buying HSN.

01:54:18.609 --> 01:54:21.949
It's all about HSN now,
and he wants you to come with him.

01:54:24.364 --> 01:54:25.914
He needs you.

01:54:26.700 --> 01:54:28.790
You're going to be very big over there.

01:54:29.286 --> 01:54:31.246
That's what's going to happen.

01:54:31.663 --> 01:54:34.463
But, you didn't hear it from me, right?

01:54:35.083 --> 01:54:39.253
No, I sure didn't.
But thank you.

01:54:42.591 --> 01:54:44.631
It's nice to see you.

01:54:44.676 --> 01:54:46.256
It's good to see you.

01:54:48.555 --> 01:54:50.715
I'll see you around, pal.

01:54:50.766 --> 01:54:52.726
Yeah.

01:54:59.900 --> 01:55:01.110
It's been a long journey.

01:55:01.151 --> 01:55:02.281
Yes, it has.

01:55:02.319 --> 01:55:03.449
I'm proud of you.

01:55:03.487 --> 01:55:04.697
Thank you, Neil.

01:55:38.856 --> 01:55:42.396
This right here,
this is a special power.

01:55:44.278 --> 01:55:46.148
This is a special power.

01:55:50.868 --> 01:55:54.158
And then I started
to build my very own house...

01:55:55.914 --> 01:55:58.674
where I would live
and make wonderful creations...

01:55:58.709 --> 01:56:02.049
for all the world to see and love.

01:56:07.718 --> 01:56:10.348
She didn't know any of this would happen...

01:56:10.387 --> 01:56:13.257
as she walked that day.

